    {
      "title": "When to choose which GC",
      "content": "Default (Java 9+): G1 — good balance for most apps. Latency-critical microservices (<10ms pause target): ZGC or Shenandoah. Batch/throughput jobs: Parallel GC. Very small apps / embedded: Serial GC. Benchmarking (eliminate GC from measurements): Epsilon GC. Upgrade path: Serial → Parallel → G1 → ZGC/Shenandoah."
    }
